item.description:
When we started talking about a dev blog among us, we thought about who could write, what we wanted to talk about, who was going to review the articles&hellip;
Technically, WordPress was the first solution we reviewed but after giving it more thought we realized it would be too much of a hassle to maintain: plugin updates, core updates, database backups, security issues, etc.
We then came up with a better idea: Jekyll.
